body:
Tested https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/1114:

Grpc.IntegrationTesting.Client.exe shuts down cleanly, as far as I can tell. Yay!
Grpc.IntegrationTesting.Server.exe stops by crashing vshost32.exe ("vshost32.exe has stopped working") - exit code 0x4000001f :

Last line of log:

> src\core\iomgr\tcp_windows.c:129: on_read

Edit: Used the native debugger to track it into grpc_csharp_ext.dll:

Callstack:

>   grpc_csharp_ext.dll!on_read(void \* tcpp, int success) Line 134  C
>     grpc_csharp_ext.dll!do_iocp_work(...) Line 121  C
>     grpc_csharp_ext.dll!iocp_loop(void \* p) Line 128    C
>     grpc_csharp_ext.dll!thread_body(void \* v) Line 54   C

Code tcp_windows.c - __debugbreak() is triggered:

>   gpr_log(GPR_DEBUG, "on_read");
>   tcp->outstanding_read = 0;
>   if (socket->read_info.wsa_error != 0) {
>     char *utf8_message = gpr_format_message(info->wsa_error);
>     __debugbreak(); // <-------- That's the one!
>     gpr_log(GPR_ERROR, "ReadFile overlapped error: %s", utf8_message);
>     gpr_free(utf8_message);
>     status = GRPC_ENDPOINT_CB_ERROR;
>   } else {

utf8_message reads:

> "An existing connection was forcibly closed by the remote host.\r\n"
